13.There is a biker going on a road trip. The road trip consists of n + 1 points at various altitudes. The biker starts his trip on point 0 with altitude equal 0.
You are given an integer array gain of length n where gain[i] is the net gain in altitude between points i​​​​​​ and i + 1 for all (0 <= i < n). Return the highest altitude of a point.
Platform : Leetcode 
SOURCECODE : class Solution {
    public int largestAltitude(int[] gain) {
        int alt = 0;
        int current = 0;    
        int n = gain.length;

        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {

            current = current + gain[i];   

            if (current > alt) {           
                alt = current;
            }
        }

        return alt;
    }
}

